com.bmwcarit.barefoot.markov

Class Factory<C extends StateCandidate<C,T,S>,T extends StateTransition,S extends Sample>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.bmwcarit.barefoot.markov.Factory<C,T,S>
  • Type Parameters:
    C - Candidate inherits from StateCandidate.
    T - Transition inherits from StateTransition.
    S - Sample inherits from Sample.
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    MatcherFactory

    public abstract class Factory<C extends StateCandidate<C,T,S>,T extends StateTransition,S extends Sample>
extends Object
    Factory for creation of state candidates, which is StateCandidate, transitions, which is StateTransition, and samples, i.e. Sample. A Factory instance enables dependency injection during creation from their respective JSON representation.
